OL,3,CTerror attack survivors face rising
OL,4,Conline abuse and death threats, report
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FSurvivors of terror attacks are being
OL,8,Fhit by a wave of online abuse, and are
OL,9,Ffacing trolling, harassment, malicious
OL,10,Fmessages and even death threats
OL,11,Ffuelled by social media, a new report
OL,12,Fwarns.
OL,14,FThe report by Survivors Against Terror
OL,15,F(SAT), released on Friday, found
OL,16,Fvictims are often personally targeted,
OL,17,Fwhile images of attacks, sometimes
OL,18,Fposted by perpetrators of the crime or
OL,19,Ftheir supporters, are widely shared
OL,20,Fand reshared, retraumatising those
OL,21,Faffected.
