OL,3,CTerror attack survivors face rising
OL,4,Conline abuse and death threats, report
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FThe research shows more than two-
OL,8,Fthirds (67%) of survivors saw social
OL,9,Fmedia content related to the attack
OL,10,Fthey experienced - of those, 97% said
OL,11,Fit was harmful or distressing.
OL,13,FAlmost half (45%) had their personal
OL,14,Fphotos or videos taken from social
OL,15,Fmedia, while 35% said their stories
OL,16,Fwere used in conspiracy theories. A
OL,17,Ffurther 25% reported having their
OL,18,Fimages manipulated online.
