OL,4,Conline abuse and death threats, report
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FThe report also found that more than
OL,8,Fhalf (52%) of survivors saw their
OL,9,Ffamily or friends contacted or
OL,10,Ftargeted on social media after the
OL,11,Fattack, while 41% witnessed other
OL,12,Fsurvivors being harassed.
OL,14,FOne in six (17%) said they had been
OL,15,Fsent images of deceased loved ones,
OL,16,Fhate-filled messages, accusations of
OL,17,Fbeing "crisis actors", or death
OL,18,Fthreats.
