OL,3,CTerror attack survivors face rising
OL,4,Conline abuse and death threats, report
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FAnother co-author of the report, Dr
OL,8,FBethan Davies of Cardiff University,
OL,9,Fsaid: "Our research has found that, at
OL,10,Fa time of shock, distress and grief,
OL,11,Fsocial media presents a profound
OL,12,Fchallenge for survivors of terror
OL,13,Fattacks.
OL,15,F"Not only does it mean survivors may
OL,16,Fbe unexpectedly exposed to content
OL,17,Fabout the attack, with images and
OL,18,Fvideos posted online reminding them of
OL,19,Ftheir traumatic experiences and loss,
OL,20,Fbut social media can lead to various
OL,21,Fforms of intrusion and abuse."
